the morrison institute winter colloquium presents jonathan pritchard population variation and epigenetic controls of gene expression events at stanford the morrison institute winter colloquium presents jonathan pritchard population variation and epigenetic controls of gene expression facebook twitter email print add to calendar it is becoming increasingly clear that genetic variation in gene regulation plays a central role in evolution and in the genetics of complex traits however it remains extremely difficult to predict which variants in the genome may impact gene regulation hence the mapping of expression quantitative trait loci eqtls has emerged as an important tool for linking genetic variation to changes in gene regulation in this talk professor pritchard will describe recent work that his group has done towards understanding the mechanisms by which eqtls act and discuss how they might ultimately predict which variants are most likely to have regulatory activity jonathan pritchard is a professor in the department of human genetics the committees on genetics and evolutionary biology at the university of chicago and he is an investigator at the howard hughes medical institute he earned his ph d at stanford under the mentorship of professor marcus feldman who is director of the morrison institute for population and resource studies when wednesday february 22 2012 4 15 pm approximate duration of 1.25 hour s where herrin hall t 175 map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends tags lecture reading health wellness public service sponsor morrison institute for population and resource studies contact 723 7518 morrisoninstitute stanford edu admission free open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 310 31049 last modified february 17 2012
